## An extremely short into to Signal detection theory (SDT)

  - SDT provides separate measures of sensitivity and bias bias (Green & Swets, 1966).
  - _d'_ is a measure of sensitivity or discriminability
  - criterion, often stated as _c_, is a measure of bias

